:::summary
Philosophy and theology are the great disciplines of human inquiry into truth, existence, and the nature of God. While philosophy asks questions about reality using reason alone, theology brings divine revelation into conversation with reason. From the perspective of Latter-day Saint thought, both are valuable tools — but revelation is the supreme source of truth, and the restored gospel provides answers that the greatest philosophers only glimpsed.
:::

